    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fijian-style-lime-and-coconut-pollock-curry-and-rice-with-broccoli-side/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Dice your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>finely</p><p>Zest <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lime[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter) then cut into wedges</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and shake off the excess water</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fijian-style-lime-and-coconut-pollock-curry-and-rice-with-broccoli-side/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick, with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced tomato[es]</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softening</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fijian-style-lime-and-coconut-pollock-curry-and-rice-with-broccoli-side/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softening, add your <strong>curry powder</strong> and <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fijian-style-lime-and-coconut-pollock-curry-and-rice-with-broccoli-side/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>cultured coconut</strong> with your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up until completely combined</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fijian-style-lime-and-coconut-pollock-curry-and-rice-with-broccoli-side/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>pollock bites </strong>(Tip: Unevely sized pollock bites? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!) to the curry sauce, and cook, covered, for 4-5 min further or until the fish is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fijian-style-lime-and-coconut-pollock-curry-and-rice-with-broccoli-side/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once your pollock is cooked through, add your <strong>ginger paste</strong> to the pan with the <strong>lime zest</strong>, a squeeze of <strong>lime juice </strong>and<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and gently stir it all together</p><p>Add the <strong>spinach</strong>, cover with the lid and cook for a final 1-2 min or until wilted, then give everything a gentle mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>Fijian-style lime & coconut pollock curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fijian-style-lime-and-coconut-pollock-curry-and-rice-with-broccoli-side/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Fijian-style lime & coconut pollock curry</strong> over the <strong>cooked rice</strong> and garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
